<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-07T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4144. Your 5271, December 5, 5 p. m. Department has never understood
                                that arrangements contained in your 4755,<note n="3" xml:id="d649fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_512">p.
                                    512</ref>.</note> August 22, or 5076,<note n="1" xml:id="d649fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_519">p.
                                    519</ref>.</note> October 26, were intended to supplant
                                assurances contained in <pb facs="0808" n="522" xml:id="pg_522"/>
                                your 4661,<note n="1" xml:id="d649fn3">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_512">p.
                                    512</ref>.</note> August 5, as to tobacco on high seas or loaded
                                and then awaiting shipment. So inform Foreign Office and make
                                vigorous representations as instructed in Department’s 4110,<note n="2" xml:id="d649fn4">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_520">p.
                                    520</ref>.</note> December 1.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>